{{DISPLAYTITLE:/etc/portage/package.accept_keywords}}

{{Path|package.accept_keywords}} and {{Path|package.keywords}} are files or directories of files containing definitions for per-package <code>ACCEPT_KEYWORDS</code> statements. They are useful for mixing unstable packages in with a normally stable system packages or vice versa.

These two locations allow <code>ACCEPT_KEYWORDS</code> to be augmented for single packages. If both {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} and {{Path|package.keywords}} are present, both will be used; values from {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} will override values from {{Path|package.keywords}}. The {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} location is intended to replace the {{Path|package.keywords}} location, since profiles support a different form of {{Path|package.keywords}} which modifies effective {{Keyword|KEYWORDS}} (rather than <code>ACCEPT_KEYWORDS</code>).

== Format and examples ==

* Comment lines begin with <code>#</code> (no inline comments)
* One DEPEND atom per line followed by additional {{Keyword|KEYWORDS}}
* Lines without any {{Keyword|KEYWORDS}} imply unstable host arch

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.accept_keywords|title=package.accept_keywords example|1=

# Always use unstable libgd
media-libs/libgd ~x86

# Only use stable mplayer
media-video/mplayer -~x86

# Always use unstable netcat
net-analyzer/netcat
}}

Note: In addition to the normal values from <code>ACCEPT_KEYWORDS</code> {{Path|package.keywords}} supports three special tokens:

* <code>*</code>  Package is visible if it is stable on any architecture
* <code>~*</code> Package is visible if it is in testing on any architecture
* <code>**</code> Package is always visible ({{Keyword|KEYWORDS}} are ignored completely)

Additional Note: If you encounter the <code>-* {{Keyword|KEYWORD}}</code>, this indicates that the package is known to be broken on all systems which are not otherwise listed in {{Keyword|KEYWORDS}}. For example, a binary only package which is built for {{Keyword|x86}} will look like:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.accept_keywords|title=Broken on all but x86 example|1=
games-fps/quake3-demo-1.11.ebuild:KEYWORDS="-* x86"
}}

To accept this package anyway, use one of the other keywords in {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} like this:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.accept_keywords|title=Accept anyways example|1=
games-fps/quake3-demo x86
}}

